OL,3,CPremier League spending cap backed by
OL,4,Cmost clubs but will the richest agree?
OL,6,FMan Utd said they are worried it'll
OL,7,Frisk undermining their competitiveness
OL,8,Fagainst European sides.
OL,10,FAston Villa are also reported to have
OL,11,Fvoted against, with Chelsea reported
OL,12,Fto have abstained.
OL,14,FAnchoring faces some major obstacles
OL,15,Fbefore it can be fully adopted, not
OL,16,Fleast the backing of the Professional
OL,17,FFootballers' Association which said on
OL,18,FMonday it would "oppose any measure
OL,19,Fthat would place a 'hard' cap on
OL,20,Fplayer wages".
