OL,3,CPremier League spending cap backed by
OL,4,Cmost clubs but will the richest agree?
OL,6,FUnited oppose the concept of anchoring
OL,7,Fbecause they feel the measure unfairly
OL,8,Fpenalises them for their success in
OL,9,Fgenerating large, self-sustaining
OL,10,Frevenues which they have built over
OL,11,Fdecades of sporting achievement and
OL,12,Fcommercial innovation.
OL,14,FThe club are also understood to be
OL,15,Fconcerned that measures to level out
OL,16,Fcompetition in the Premier League risk
OL,17,Fundermining the competitiveness of
OL,18,FEnglish clubs in relation to their
OL,19,FEuropean peers and weaken the Premier
OL,20,FLeague as a global force.
